# Bug check workflow

When the user says **bug check** (or similar: "fix bugs till clean", "bug check till clean"):

1. Audit all source files — app, widget extension, shared services, storage, intents, Xcode project.
2. Fix real bugs: crashes, race conditions, broken sharing (App Group/Keychain), API edge cases, widget layout issues, empty pickers, stale dead code.
3. Keep fixes minimal and focused; match existing code style.
4. Re-scan after fixes; repeat until no meaningful issues remain.
5. Summarize what was fixed and what the user should rebuild/test on Mac/iPhone.

Do not stop after one pass if obvious issues remain.
